The data overwhelmingly reveals that remote work is better for business. According to a recent report, 74 percent of employees and 75 percent of senior leaders report heightened productivity in remote work environments, citing avoiding burnout, improved ability to perform, less anxiety, and avoiding office politics as the biggest drivers. Furthermore, 81 percent of employees say they are less likely to be forced to choose between family and career. If companies force employees back into the office, the report warns they will see decreased engagement and increased attrition. Over 50 percent of respondents said they would require at least a 30 percent raise to return to the office.
